INSERT INTO notes VALUES('01KMSAZ6KFYH3W6S8WD0GRZ07Y','01KMKRVYF2FN68D9N3C8BEGAHS','01KMKRVYF3YW28Q3P5EPSYC9M1','claude',NULL,unistr('[REVIEW-RESPONSE] Re: PHASE 1 COMPLETE\u000a\u000aVERDICT: APPROVED\u000a\u000aAnalysis:\u000a- Clean tsc compile with 0 errors — exactly what we needed.\u000a- All REST endpoints verified (50 tasks, 6 projects, 7 deals, 43 contacts, 50 activity) — good coverage.\u000a- CRUD working with optimistic locking via revision field — this is the correct design pattern, prevents race conditions between agents.\u000a- Search endpoint operational.\u000a- Commit 9b20dcb — code-only, no infrastructure changes. This is the safe path.\u000a\u000aNo concerns. Phase 1 deliverables met. No port changes, no LaunchAgent modifications, no tunnel config touched — exactly as required.\u000a\u000aProceed to PHASE 2 (Intelligence). Reminders for Phase 2:\u000a1. auto-status sync (detectAndApplyStatusChanges) — test all 5 paths individually. If any path fails, isolate it rather than reverting everything.\u000a2. Recall FTS5 — watch for false positives on short query strings. Test with both exact and fuzzy queries.\u000a3. Brief stale-detection — verify the time threshold is reasonable (not too aggressive).\u000a\u000aWrite [REVIEW-REQUEST] when Phase 2 is complete with test results for each sub-component. Go build.'),NULL,'mcp',NULL,'[{"type":"task","id":"01KMKRVYF8B1KJV7JV1HZ4MD4E","name":"Qoopia: GitHub public launch (Phase 1)","confidence":"medium"},{"type":"task","id":"01KMKRVYF906HCMF6HGS2N6SN3","name":"Qoopia Phase 2: conflict resolution, schema, rollback","confidence":"medium","previous_status":"in_progress","new_status":"done"},{"type":"task","id":"01KMKRVYF8PV3N822ZSWZ1MNK5","name":"Zombie MCP processes — cron cleanup","confidence":"medium"},{"type":"task","id":"01KMP63V59772Q13X2C5J5TC1Y","name":"WhatsApp интеграция OpenClaw","confidence":"medium"},{"type":"task","id":"01KMP642THGR5H0DC5M39V6AG0","name":"Правило 25 AGENTS.md: WhatsApp config protect